{
  format: 1
  name: set-compared-as-sorted-member-sequence
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["#annex-b", "§B.4", "§B.1"]
  tags: ["ordering"]
  note: '''
    §B.4 set: "sort members by element order, then compare the resulting member
    sequences". A set has no authored order, so its comparison key is the
    member sequence sorted by the element type's order (§B.1 text). Attack:
    hope a set's sort position depends on the order members were inserted, or
    on set size/hash. It must not — {"c","a"} and {"a","c"} are the same value
    and both compare as the sequence [a,c].

    Seeded sets (insertion order deliberately scrambled) and their sorted
    member sequences:
      {c,a}  -> [a,c]
      {a,b}  -> [a,b]
      {b,c}  -> [b,c]
    Sequence comparison (all length 2, so no length ambiguity is invoked):
      [a,b] < [a,c]   differ at position 2: b < c
      [a,c] < [b,c]   differ at position 1: a < b
    Correct ascending order of the owning rows: r_ab, r_ca, r_bc.
  '''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.annexb.set@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      rows: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        tags: { $set: "text" }
      }
      $public: {
        by_tags: { $view: ".rows { id, tags, $sort: [tags] }" }
      }
    }
    $data: {
      rows: {
        r_ca: { tags: ["c", "a"] }
        r_ab: { tags: ["b", "a"] }
        r_bc: { tags: ["c", "b"] }
      }
    }
  }

  steps: [
    { watch: "public.by_tags", id: "w1",
      expect_init: { value: [
        { id: "r_ab", tags: ["a", "b"] }
        { id: "r_ca", tags: ["a", "c"] }
        { id: "r_bc", tags: ["b", "c"] }
      ] } }
  ]
}
